\b0\fs26 \cf0 The cameras in the field have their data collected by the SiteProxy software. SiteProxy also archives that data in an FTP server. The data in the FTP server is made available via an API through a REST server. The Cameras app uses that API to make structured requests to build up the data it displays.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl440\sa254

\b\fs44 \cf0 Library Dependencies\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa382

\b0\fs26 \cf0 The Cameras uses {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://cocoapods.org/"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 CocoaPods}} for library management.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl560\sa254

\b\fs58 \cf0 Components\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa382

\b0\fs26 \cf0 The app uses {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://cocoadocs.org/docsets/AFNetworking"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 AFNetworking}} for its network library. The data is stored in an {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/CoreData/Reference/NSFetchedResultsController_Class/Reference/Reference.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 NSFetchedResultsController}} and the controller sorts, indexes, and sections the data. The sectioned data is then displayed using a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/uikit/reference/UICollectionView_class/Reference/Reference.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 UICollectionViewController}} that displays the photos in a grid sectioned according to regions and sites in those regions.\
